# Cloudflare Pages security headers for the Gecko Creationz app.
# Cloudflare reads this file at the root of the deploy and applies the
# headers to every response. Reference:
# https://developers.cloudflare.com/pages/configuration/headers/
#
# Rules below are intentionally conservative — they harden against common
# attacks (clickjacking, MIME sniffing, mixed content) without breaking
# the existing inline-script architecture. If we add a strict
# Content-Security-Policy later, we'll need to refactor inline scripts
# first.

/*
  Strict-Transport-Security: max-age=31536000; includeSubDomains; preload
  X-Content-Type-Options: nosniff
  X-Frame-Options: SAMEORIGIN
  Referrer-Policy: strict-origin-when-cross-origin
  Permissions-Policy: camera=(self), microphone=(), geolocation=(), payment=()
  Cross-Origin-Opener-Policy: same-origin
